  "calibration_note": "THIS IS A MEASUREMENT GAP, NOT A DECLINE. Fidelity Investments has never been individually assessed; its published 62.5 is a bulk-import placeholder that assigned a flat 3.5 to all eight dimensions. This first 40-subdimension review produces a dimension average of about 3.05, and essentially the entire -11.2 point gap comes from that arithmetic difference. The within-window evidence is mild: a $2.5 million settlement of a 2024 data breach affecting about 77,000 people, resolved with genuinely reasonable remedies, and a five-day return-to-office mandate. Neither is a compassion failure of the kind that would justify an 11-point drop. This is the documented scrutiny bias described in research/US_STATES_REASSESSMENT_RUNBOOK.md: adversarial review finds gaps that flat batch assignment never looked for. Recommendation is flag-for-review rather than downgrade, because the correct remedy is a cohort-wide calibration of never-assessed Fortune 500 placeholders, not a one-off cut to Fidelity while its actual conduct record for the period is unremarkable to good.",
